<section class="section" id="problem" aria-labelledby="problem-title">
  <h2 id="problem-title">The Problem</h2>
  <p>Filament-only math misses true print cost. Real prints depend on more than grams used.</p>
  <div class="section-grid">
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Filament Alone Is Incomplete</h3>
      <p>Many makers only price by grams used, which underestimates final cost.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Electricity Is Printer-Specific</h3>
      <p>Power draw varies by machine and print length, and can materially change total cost.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Multiple Materials Change Totals</h3>
      <p>Mixed-material prints need more than one filament input to stay accurate.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Advanced Pricing Needs Extra Controls</h3>
      <p>Labour, failure risk, markup, and setup fees matter when you need business pricing.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

