<section class="section faq" id="faq" aria-labelledby="faq-title">
  <h2 id="faq-title">FAQ</h2>
  <details>
    <summary>Does the app require internet?</summary>
    <p>No. The app is offline-first with no account required and no cloud dependency.</p>
  </details>
  <details>
    <summary>Can I use more than one printer?</summary>
    <p>Yes. Free includes up to 2 printer profiles. Premium removes that cap.</p>
  </details>
  <details>
    <summary>Can I export my data?</summary>
    <p>Yes. Single-job export is included in Free and Premium. Premium also includes bulk/full history export and batch quote export.</p>
  </details>
  <details>
    <summary>Can I back up and restore my app data?</summary>
    <p>Yes. JSON backup and restore are available in Free and Premium, so you can keep a portable copy of your setup without a cloud account.</p>
  </details>
  <details>
    <summary>How do materials work in Free?</summary>
    <p>Free includes up to 5 saved materials. You can still cost a print with up to 1 Unsaved Material per calculation, so the saved-material cap does not block calculator use.</p>
  </details>
  <details>
    <summary>What kind of batch costing is included in Free?</summary>
    <p>Free includes manual batch costing for up to 3 items per batch. Premium adds unlimited batch costing and batch G-code import.</p>
  </details>
  <details>
    <summary>Rated vs Average wattage — what's the difference?</summary>
    <p>Rated wattage is the maximum your printer can draw from the wall (printed on the nameplate). Average wattage is its typical power during a print, ideally measured with a plug-in meter. Use Average for accurate electricity cost, or Rated as a safe upper bound.</p>
    <p>Long prints and high-wattage printers can significantly impact cost. Ignoring this leads to underpricing.</p>
  </details>
  <details>
    <summary>Is my data stored in the cloud?</summary>
    <p>No. Data stays on your device and the app does not depend on cloud storage for core use.</p>
  </details>
  <details>
    <summary>What happens if I downgrade and I am over the Free limits?</summary>
    <p>Your existing saved materials, printer profiles, and history entries remain intact, viewable, and editable. New creates or imports beyond the Free caps are blocked.</p>
  </details>
</section>

